HORIZONWORKS NEW HIRE: FIRST WEEK SCHEDULE TEMPLATE
====================================================
HR Onboarding Team | Last Updated: December 2025

Welcome to HorizonWorks! Your first week is designed to help you get 
oriented, meet your team, and set you up for success. Your manager will 
customize this template with specific meetings and activities.

========================================================================
DAY 1 - MONDAY: WELCOME & SETUP
========================================================================

9:00 AM - 9:30 AM    Welcome Coffee with Manager
                     Location: Your manager's preferred spot
                     Purpose: Informal hello, day overview

9:30 AM - 11:00 AM   IT Setup
                     Location: Your desk
                     Purpose: Laptop configuration, accounts
                     Bring: Personal phone for MFA setup

11:00 AM - 12:00 PM  HR Orientation (Virtual)
                     Link: Sent via calendar invite
                     Topics: Benefits enrollment, policies, Workday setup

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM   Lunch with Team
                     Location: TBD by manager
                     Purpose: Meet immediate teammates

1:00 PM - 2:00 PM    Workstation Setup
                     Location: Your desk
                     Purpose: Organize space, desk supplies, ergonomics check

2:00 PM - 3:00 PM    Manager 1:1
                     Location: Manager's office or video call
                     Topics: 30/60/90 day expectations, questions

3:00 PM - 4:30 PM    Security Training (Required)
                     Location: Self-paced, your desk
                     Note: Must complete Day 1 modules

4:30 PM - 5:00 PM    End of Day Check-in with Manager
                     Purpose: Questions, tomorrow preview

========================================================================
DAY 2 - TUESDAY: LEARNING THE BUSINESS
========================================================================

9:00 AM - 10:00 AM   Company Overview Presentation (Virtual)
                     Presenter: People Team
                     Topics: History, mission, values, org structure

10:00 AM - 11:00 AM  Product Deep Dive (Virtual)
                     Presenter: Product Team
                     Topics: What we build, who uses it, roadmap

11:00 AM - 12:00 PM  Department Orientation
                     With: Department head or designee
                     Topics: Team structure, key projects, how you fit

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM   Lunch (on your own or with buddy)

1:00 PM - 2:00 PM    Meet Your Onboarding Buddy
                     Location: Coffee or video call
                     Purpose: Your go-to for "silly" questions

2:00 PM - 3:30 PM    Systems Training
                     Self-paced at your desk
                     Topics: Slack, Notion, tools specific to role

3:30 PM - 4:30 PM    Benefits Deep Dive (Optional but Recommended)
                     Virtual session with HR
                     Topics: Health plans, 401(k), perks

4:30 PM - 5:00 PM    Reflection Time
                     Purpose: Review notes, write down questions

========================================================================
DAY 3 - WEDNESDAY: MEETING THE TEAM
========================================================================

9:00 AM - 9:30 AM    Morning Check-in with Manager

9:30 AM - 12:00 PM   Cross-functional Intros (30 min each)
                     [Manager will schedule relevant stakeholders]
                     Example: Partner team leads, key collaborators

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM   New Hire Lunch (All new hires this month)
                     Location: Calendar invite from HR
                     Purpose: Meet your cohort

1:00 PM - 2:00 PM    ERG Overview (Optional)
                     Presenter: DEI Team
                     Topics: Employee Resource Groups, how to join

2:00 PM - 4:00 PM    Role-Specific Onboarding
                     [Varies by department - manager will schedule]
                     Examples: Codebase walkthrough, CRM training, etc.

4:00 PM - 5:00 PM    Q&A with Onboarding Buddy

========================================================================
DAY 4 - THURSDAY: GOING DEEPER
========================================================================

9:00 AM - 10:00 AM   Culture & Values Session (Virtual)
                     Presenter: People Team
                     Topics: Our values in practice, norms, feedback culture

10:00 AM - 12:00 PM  Role-Specific Training (Continued)
                     [Manager to customize]

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM   Lunch

1:00 PM - 2:00 PM    IT Security Training (Complete remaining modules)

2:00 PM - 3:00 PM    Manager 1:1: Week So Far
                     Topics: Questions, initial impressions, adjustments

3:00 PM - 4:30 PM    Begin First Project/Task
                     Your manager will assign a starter project
                     Purpose: Learn by doing

4:30 PM - 5:00 PM    Explore Notion/Internal Resources

========================================================================
DAY 5 - FRIDAY: WRAPPING UP WEEK 1
========================================================================

9:00 AM - 10:00 AM   Finish Outstanding Trainings
                     Ensure all Day 1-5 requirements complete

10:00 AM - 11:00 AM  New Hire AMA with Leadership (Virtual)
                     Monthly session with a senior leader
                     Purpose: Ask anything, hear from leadership

11:00 AM - 12:00 PM  Week 1 Reflection with Manager
                     Topics: Wins, challenges, goals for Week 2

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM   Lunch

1:00 PM - 4:00 PM    Flex Time
                     Continue role onboarding, starter project, or
                     catch up on reading/training

4:00 PM - 4:30 PM    Complete Week 1 Feedback Survey
                     Link sent via email
                     Purpose: Help us improve onboarding

4:30 PM - 5:00 PM    Wrap Up & Weekend Send-off

